<ul><li>Due to the ionisation of the air, an&nbsp;\(\alpha\)&nbsp;or&nbsp;\(\beta\)&nbsp;particle passing through the cloud chamber&nbsp;<b>leaves a visible track</b>&nbsp;of condensed vapour droplets.</li><li>Because the air space is&nbsp;<b>supersaturated</b>, when an ionising particle passes through the supersaturated vapour, the ions produced&nbsp;<b>trigger the formation of droplets</b>.</li></ul>